Seven?

9
00:01:47,330 --> 00:01:48,430
Three to go.

10
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:50,160
Glad we have the number now.

11
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,630
The wedding in Cao Village

12
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,230
is really glorious.

13
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:22,860
The feast will last three days.

14
00:02:23,130 --> 00:02:24,460
Yesterday, on the market,

15
00:02:24,530 --> 00:02:25,630
the pork was sold out.

16
00:02:25,660 --> 00:02:27,360
The Cao family had bought all of it.

17
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:28,500
That's right.

18
00:02:28,730 --> 00:02:31,460
I heard those who worked outside

19
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,760
were on their way back.

20
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,430
Why is Qingshan so popular?

21
00:02:36,930 --> 00:02:37,960
You don't know, huh?

22
00:02:38,330 --> 00:02:39,900
Villagers there had a kiln for a living.

23
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,700
Over twenty years ago,
the kiln exploded.

24
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:43,960
Qingshan's parents lost their lives

25
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:44,830
to save others.

26
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:46,600
The villagers were grateful

27
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,460
and took care of him,
one way or another.

28
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:50,200
This time, the whole village

29
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:51,460
contributes to his wedding.

30
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,560
Well, Qingshan is quite lucky.

31
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:56,300
A lot of guys work in town.

32
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,800
Only he brought back a wife from there.

33
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,500
I've heard that's a pretty girl.

34
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:01,530
Taste it.

35
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:06,500
Can I use it?

36
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:07,360
Yes.

37
00:03:15,530 --> 00:03:16,160
Hello?

38
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,860
Thirteen, it's me.

39
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,930
Cao? How's everything going?

40
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,960
Here's the thing.

41
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,830
These days,

42
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:23,960
it's been raining heavily.

43
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,460
There are even mudslides

44
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,560
and the roads are blocked.

45
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,900
The worst is that the base station
is broken too.

46
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,130
So now, I have to go

47
00:03:30,130 --> 00:03:31,600
a really long way into the village.

48
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,860
What's worse, there's no signal.

49
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:34,700
Sounds terrible.

50
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,460
Be careful during your investigation.

51
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,030
Don't act rashly.

52
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,060
Stay alert.

53
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,760
Call me every day.

54
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,460
If necessary, call the police.

55
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:45,030
There's a phone
outside the village, right?

56
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,030
Yes, I'm using it now.

57
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,360
Despite the long way,

58
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,960
you'll get there, gasping and panting.

59
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,600
It's easy for you to say.

60
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:58,360
How much?

61
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,130
Ten yuan.

62
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:00,200
What?

63
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,100
Ten.

64
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,330
[Payphone: 10 yuan per minute]

65
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:08,160
I can't make too many calls, then.

66
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:10,300
Here's the money.

67
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:11,360
Let's go.

68
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:13,860
Goodbye, sir.

69
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:14,730
See you.

70
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:21,600
Mr. Shi, a bottle of water, please.

71
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,060
And you are...?

72
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:25,760
I'm Jinhua,

73
00:04:28,430 --> 00:04:29,400
Cao Jinhua.

74
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:31,300
Oh, Tubby.

75
00:04:31,530 --> 00:04:32,560
Yes, it's me.

76
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,530
It's been a few years.

77
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:36,600
You look prettier.

78
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,360
I do, don't I?

79
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:38,960
Oh, Mr. Shi.

80
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:40,960
Don't call me Cao Jinhua.

81
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,160
I've changed my name.

82
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:43,600
It's Jenny.

83
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:44,130
Je...

84
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,700
Jenny.

85
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:46,330
Je...

86
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,500
All right, Mr. Shi.

87
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,200
Just call me Janni Cao.

88
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,600
Water, please.

89
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:51,400
Okay.

90
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:52,830
How much?

91
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:54,330
It's on the house.

92
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:55,230
You're too kind.

93
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:56,430
Just enjoy it.

94
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:58,030
Thanks, Mr. Shi.

95
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,230
I won't keep you long.

96
00:04:59,260 --> 00:05:00,230
Bye, Mr. Shi.

97
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:06,400
Jenny?

