105
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,160
Qingshan.

106
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:03,730
Come here.

107
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:05,260
It's me.

108
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:07,860
Yanhua!

109
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,000
Why didn't you tell me

110
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:13,530
you were coming back?

111
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:15,130
I thought you wouldn't come.

112
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,900
Come on. Get in here.

113
00:06:17,530 --> 00:06:19,430
It's been about six years
since we last met.

114
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:20,960
You're getting chubbier.

115
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:22,700
Did you see your parents?

116
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,060
Here's the thing.

117
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,730
Marriage

118
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,260
is a big thing for you.

119
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,660
It's once in a lifetime.

120
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:32,230
As your cousin, I must come back,

121
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,860
but I won't see my parents.

122
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,900
Only you know I'm back here.

123
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:41,160
It's been so many years
after you ran away from your wedding.

124
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,830
Your parents don't mind it any more.

125
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,560
I guess they are decorating

126
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:46,330
the wedding scene in the square.

127
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,500
How about this?

128
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,760
We'll go there together.

129
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,130
No, no. Calm down.

130
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:52,830
I'm back

131
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:54,200
only for two things.

132
00:06:54,830 --> 00:06:55,600
First,

133
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:56,800
I want to take a good look at you

134
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:58,000
and give you some lucky money.

135
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,160
Wow.

136
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,500
Aren't you a handsome guy now?

137
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:05,000
Second, I'll meet your wife.

138
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,560
Then I'll leave.

139
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,400
Fine then.

140
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:11,900
Come on in. Take a rest

141
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,600
and grab something to eat.

142
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:14,700
I'll lock the door.

143
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:19,930
You came back here

144
00:07:19,930 --> 00:07:20,860
without telling me.

145
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,060
You must've got caught in the rain.

146
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:23,230
Let's go.

147
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,060
It's a sudden rain, indeed.

148
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,560
Yanhua,

149
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:28,300
the steps are slippery.

150
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,460
Be very careful.

151
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,900
When you were little,
you flushed when you met a girl.

152
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,160
Now, you're getting married before me.

153
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,230
I heard you met that girl

154
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,030
when you were working in town.

155
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,100
What's her name?

156
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:44,130
Yafeng.

157
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:45,830
She's pretty.

158
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,030
I don't know why,

159
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,100
but she's in love with me.

160
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:51,700
Don't show off.

161
00:07:56,660 --> 00:07:59,400
Why are both the front
and the back doors locked?

162
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,830
They used to be open.

163
00:08:01,030 --> 00:08:01,900
They were open

164
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,560
because we had nothing valuable.

165
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,200
But now, things have changed.

166
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:06,130
It makes sense.

167
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,130
All right. Let's get in.

168
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,400
When I'm done with the trifles,

169
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,930
I'll take you to see Yafeng.

170
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,960
She's very shy of people.

171
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,300
Can I see her?

172
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:29,630
We have a rule, after all.

173
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:32,100
The bride can't see strangers
before the wedding.

174
00:08:32,630 --> 00:08:33,560
I know.

175
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,960
But that's a rule
from the old generations.

176
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:37,660
Just don't let them find out.

177
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:39,360
Besides,

178
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,560
you aren't a stranger.

179
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:41,730
You're my cousin.

180
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:43,460
Don't worry.

181
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:46,030
Well,

182
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,030
take your time with the food.

183
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,400
I need to entertain
some guests out there.

184
00:08:48,430 --> 00:08:49,400
I should go.

185
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:50,730
Off you go.

186
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,800
I'll close the door, then.

187
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:05,060
If your parents

188
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,630
forced Qingshan to write this letter,

189
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:08,700
he would have left

190
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,000
some codes.

191
00:09:11,130 --> 00:09:11,700
Look.

192
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,930
Nothing looks weird to me.

193
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,530
I'll be relieved, then.

194
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:24,030
What's wrong?

195
00:09:25,330 --> 00:09:26,860
There are traces of some words.

196
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,500
[Save me. I'm abducted.]

197
00:10:20,930 --> 00:10:21,630
Yafeng.

198
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:52,760
Yafeng.

199
00:11:10,430 --> 00:11:11,230
Ya...

200
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,800
Yafeng.

201
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:18,900
Yafeng.

202
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:22,960
It's me.

203
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,930
I'm Cao Qingshan's cousin.

204
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,860
Are you abducted?

205
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:44,200
Help me.

206
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,300
Get me out.

207
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:28,700
It's something so serious.

208
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,730
Why did you keep the secret for him?

209
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:34,000
I didn't mean to.

210
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,630
Chubby said there was only one line.

211
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,160
If it was just a prank,

212
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,430
telling you wouldn't help.

213
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,760
If it was true,

214
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:43,100
his family would be doing a crime.

215
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,130
And he'd feel ashamed, so...

216
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,200
So, he didn't tell you.

217
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,930
How long has he been out of contact?

218
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,560
For 48 hours, I think.

219
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,460
The base station there doesn't work.

220
00:12:54,530 --> 00:12:55,360
No signal.

221
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,560
And the wedding thing.

222
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:57,600
So...

223
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,660
I can't reach him.

224
00:13:01,830 --> 00:13:03,160
It's a complicated case.

225
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:04,830
If Chubby mishandles it

226
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:06,300
and the traffickers catch him...

227
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,130
How about this?

228
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,430
I'll ask Wan Fenghuo

229
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:11,700
to inquire about the Cao Village.

230
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,030
If something's fishy,

231
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:14,400
we'll go there.

232
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,130
Okay.

233
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:37,960
Who painted this?

234
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,160
What's wrong?

235
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:40,360
Are you okay?

236
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,030
Umm...

237
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,530
I don't know.

238
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:45,360
A drunk customer, I guess.

239
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:46,800
You know how they are like.

240
00:13:46,830 --> 00:13:48,860
They break up, get divorced,
or lose their jobs.

241
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:49,430
Everything.

242
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:51,930
Maybe someone got drunk
and wanted to paint.

243
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,960
Right? Look at the numbers.

244
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,530
No normal guys would write like that.

245
00:13:55,530 --> 00:13:57,230
7786, it's...

246
00:14:00,430 --> 00:14:01,300
Are you okay?

247
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,960
I'll replace the board later.

248
00:14:05,830 --> 00:14:06,560
I'm fine.

249
00:14:08,830 --> 00:14:09,460
All right.

250
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,130
Go back and pack your things.

251
00:14:11,630 --> 00:14:12,760
If we need to go,

252
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,460
we must be prepared.

253
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,360
Why did he take a photo?

254
00:14:31,330 --> 00:14:32,430
I could do better.

255
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,600
I'll replace it tomorrow.

256
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,260
Luo.

257
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:13,700
Aoki?

258
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,160
So, did you paint the leopard?

259
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,830
You left a number
in such a complicated way.

260
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:22,330
That's not your style.

261
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:24,660
I tried to find you recently.

262
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:25,800
But you weren't in.

263
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:27,630
I have an emergency.

264
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:28,960
Tomorrow night,

265
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:30,300
at the old street.

266
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,860
I won't be available then.

267
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:34,630
You get to decide

268
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:36,560
whether to come or not.

269
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:58,800
Did Wan Fenghuo confirm
no one was abducted?

270
00:15:58,830 --> 00:15:59,960
He isn't sure about that.

271
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:00,900
But he's sure about two things.

272
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:03,500
First, there will be a big wedding.

273
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,760
A lot of people will attend.

274
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:06,760
Second,

275
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,160
the bride's name is Yafeng,

276
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,260
a girl born and raised in town.

277
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:11,230
She was a waitress in a food plaza.

278
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:13,930
Many of her friends will come too.

279
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:16,960
It doesn't sound like an abduction.

280
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:19,460
Lady Dai.

281
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:22,360
Did they

282
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,960
lure Chubby back for the marriage thing?

283
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,300
What if we arrive

284
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,830
and find that he's getting married?

285
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:29,700
Shall we offer a gift

286
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:31,830
or save the groom?

287
00:16:43,860 --> 00:16:44,800
Ready to go.

288
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:46,530
30 kilometer in total.

289
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,700
It will take 35 minutes.

